Vibe Graphing Intent: Shadow Ops Client Delivery (Package & Portal)

Model Configuration:
- Build Model (Architect): Gemini 2.0 Flash
- Invoke Model (Worker): opencode:ollama

Design Intent:
Construct an autonomous pipeline for the professional delivery of Shadow Ops solutions to the 6 identified clients. 
The system will generate branded "Engagement Packages" (HTML), provide dedicated NotebookLM links, 
and establish secure Google Doc retrieval hubs for each client. 
Ensure full business continuity by archiving all deliverables under the intellimira@gmail.com identity.

Structural Constraints (Topology):
START -> [Package_Generator] -> [Portal_Linker] -> [Delivery_Relay] -> [Vault_Archiver] -> END

Package_Generator: Creates the personalized 6-Section HTML delivery package for each client (@ninjaaitools, @officially.val, etc.).
Portal_Linker: Maps client-specific NotebookLM and Google Doc links to the delivery assets.
Delivery_Relay: Transmits the final engagement package from intellimira@gmail.com.
Vault_Archiver: Consolidates all delivered packages into .brain/outputs/client_packages/ for audit and retrieval.

Data Contracts:
- PULL: .mira/scores/shadow_ops_lineage.json, Client Emails, NotebookLM Metadata.
- PUSH: .brain/outputs/client_packages/delivery_package_*.html, .mira/scores/delivery_lineage.json.

Context Adapters:
- PathRAG: Access correspondence history and solution blueprints for package personalization.
- MCP: Utilize 'client-delivery' skill and 'lab-utility' for secure transmission.

Role Assignment:
- Generator: ✨ Creative Synthesis + ⚙️ Pragmatic Application
- Linker: ⚛️ First Principles + 🔬 Scientific Method
- Relay: ⚙️ Pragmatic Application + 🌑 The Dark Passenger
- Archiver: 🔬 Scientific Method + ⚙️ Pragmatic Application
